‘I HAVE no heart for poetry. A different passion has smitten me. I am the victim of Love in a way that no one else is. Three years ago it was Inachia. I was the talk of the town: my moody ways, my loud complaints that she preferred money to merit, my resolutions to free myself, and my repeated return to slavery. Now it is another. Neither advice nor rebuffs will cure me. The only relies that 1 can look for is some new passion.'
